race.comment: JAMARNI (2) mixing his form in Provincial company and finds a weaker contest today. Closed late when a tidy first-up third at Kembla. Then raced flat when up to the 1300m for a disappointing fifth over 1300m at Hawkesbury. Finds a weak C1 and expected to play a leading role. RAIDERLICIOUS (6) lightly raced mare who got off the mark at her second run back with a gutsy on-pace victory over 1175m at Albury. Confidence is high now and gets the right run again. CASINO SHAW (10) just over a month between runs when taken to the front for a slick victory over 1200m at the Sapphire Coast. Amy McLucas sticks and sure to go close. COMPLAISANCE (3) mixing her distances up and has the speed to get across from the awkward draw. Has further improvement to come and must be kept safe. THE EYES HAVE IT (4) consistent mare who doesn't have to improve much to take a hand in the finish.
